    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite all 7 assessed credibility factors achieving levels below required levels for MRL 5, and 6 factors flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ demonstrates 95th-percentile hemolysis remains below the clinical threshold at all operating points. The team additionally judged that the model revision issued on 2025-12-05 — three weeks after the primary experimental dataset was frozen (2025-11-14) — was not material to hemolysis prediction because the tip-clearance geometry change was small in absolute terms. No formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed to substantiate this claim.",
